race.comment: The well-related SEVENTIES HIT (2) (half to Hong Kong superstar Voyage Bubble) drifted back from the inside draw last time then found the line strongly to score by a nose over 950m at this track. Has a formidable combination with Lacey Morrison who has been aboard for his last three wins. Bold showing expected. TARGETED (7) showed good early dash last time out and led for most of the way before being claimed and finishing 1.1 lengths away in second over 1250m here. Should go well. RAETIHI (1) finished 3.5 lengths back in sixth over 1460m at Home Hill last time out after a gutsy win the start prior. Has the speed to be prominent and will be in this for a long way. KHABALOV (4) returned from a spell two weeks ago when he was beaten 2.25 lengths into ninth over 950m at this circuit. Fitter this time will prove harder to beat.
